class Solution:
    def maximumValueSum(self, b: List[List[int]]) -> int:
        # return self.max_rook_sum(b)
        m,n=len(b),len(b[0])
        ans=-float('inf')

        tem=[]
        for j in range(m):
            ir=[]
            for p in range(n):
                ir.append([b[j][p],p])
            ir=sorted(ir)[-3:]
            tem.append(ir)
        tem.sort(reverse=True)
        for i in range(m):
            ir=tem[i]
            # for p in range(n):
            #     ir.append([b[i][p],p])
            # # print(sorted(ir)[-3:])
            # ir=sorted(ir)[-3:]
            for j in range(i+1,m):
                jr=tem[j]
                # for q in range(n):
                #     jr.append([b[j][q],q])
                # # print(sorted(jr)[-3:])
                # jr=sorted(jr)[-3:]
                for k in range(j+1,m):
                    kr=tem[k]
                    # for r in range(n):
                    #     kr.append([b[k][r],r])
                    # # print(sorted(kr)[-3:])
                    # kr=sorted(kr)[-3:]

                    for a in range(3):
                        for d in range(3):
                            for c in range(3):
                                chk=[ir[a][1],jr[d][1],kr[c][1]]
                                if(len(set(chk))==3):
                                    # ans=max(ans,ir[a][0]+jr[d][0]+kr[c][0])
                                    if(ans<ir[a][0]+jr[d][0]+kr[c][0]):
                                        ans=ir[a][0]+jr[d][0]+kr[c][0]
                                        # break

        return ans
